<i>noun</i>: 흥행 [흥행], 활약상 [화략쌍], 활약 [화략], 행적 [행적], 연주 [연ː주], 연기 [연ː기], 업적 [업쩍], 성능 [성ː능], 상연 [상ː연], 놀이 [노리], 공연 [공연], 거행 [거ː행] <br>
<ul style="list-style-type:square">
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt>흥행 [흥행]</dt><br>
<dd>1. show; performance</dd><br>
<dd>돈을 받고 연극이나 영화 등을 사람들에게 보여 줌.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of showing a play or movie to the audience in return for money.</dd><br>
<dd>2. box office hit; box office success</dd><br>
<dd>연극이나 영화 등의 공연이 상업적으로 큰 수익을 거둠.</dd><br>
<dd>The state of a performance or show such as a play, movie, etc., making a big profit commercially.</dd><br>
<dt>활약상 [화략쌍]</dt><br>
<dd>activity; performance</dd><br>
<dd>활발히 활동하는 모습.</dd><br>
<dd>A state of working vigorously for something.</dd><br>
<dt>활약 [화략]</dt><br>
<dd>activity; performance; active role</dd><br>
<dd>활발히 활동함.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of playing an active part in a task.</dd><br>
<dt>행적 [행적]</dt><br>
<dd>1. trace; mark; trail</dd><br>
<dd>어떤 행위를 한 뒤에 남긴 표시나 흔적.</dd><br>
<dd>A mark or trace that one has left after having done a certain act.</dd><br>
<dd>2. achievement; accomplishment; deeds</dd><br>
<dd>평생 동안 한 일이나 업적.</dd><br>
<dd>Tasks done or achievements made during one's lifetime.</dd><br>
<dd>3. track record; performance</dd><br>
<dd>나쁜 행실로 남긴 흔적.</dd><br>
<dd>The trace left by one's bad behavior.</dd><br>
<dt>연주 [연ː주]</dt><br>
<dd>performance</dd><br>
<dd>악기를 다루어 음악을 들려줌.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of playing a musical instrument to present a piece of music.</dd><br>
<dt>연기 [연ː기]</dt><br>
<dd>acting; performance</dd><br>
<dd>배우가 맡은 역할에 따라 인물, 성격, 행동 등을 표현해 내는 것.</dd><br>
<dd>An actor or actress expressing the character, personality, behavior, etc., of a role he/she plays.</dd><br>
<dt>업적 [업쩍]</dt><br>
<dd>achievement; accomplishment; performance</dd><br>
<dd>사업이나 연구 등에서 노력과 수고를 들여 이룩해 놓은 결과.</dd><br>
<dd>Results that one achieves through endeavor and hard work in business, research, etc.</dd><br>
<dt>성능 [성ː능]</dt><br>
<dd>performance; efficiency</dd><br>
<dd>기계 등이 지닌 성질이나 기능.</dd><br>
<dd>The quality or functions of a machine, etc.</dd><br>
<dt>상연 [상ː연]</dt><br>
<dd>staging; performance</dd><br>
<dd>연극, 무용, 음악 등의 공연을 무대에서 해서 관객에게 보이는 일.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of performing a show such as a play, dance, musical performance, etc., on a stage for an audience.</dd><br>
<dt>놀이 [노리]</dt><br>
<dd>1. play; entertainment</dd><br>
<dd>즐겁게 노는 일.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of enjoying something or playing for fun.</dd><br>
<dd>2. play; entertainment; performance</dd><br>
<dd>명절이나 특별한 행사에서 여러 사람이 일정한 규칙에 따라 하는 전통 오락이나 공연.</dd><br>
<dd>A traditional Korean entertainment or performance played by a number of people according to a certain rule, on a festive day or special occasion.</dd><br>
<dd>3. game</dd><br>
<dd>일정한 규칙이나 방법에 따라 노는 일.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of playing a game according to a certain rule or method.</dd><br>
<dd>4. play</dd><br>
<dd>‘장난’이나 ‘흉내’의 뜻을 나타내는 말.</dd><br>
<dd>The word meaning 'acting in jest' or 'mimicking' something.</dd><br>
<dt>공연 [공연]</dt><br>
<dd>performance; show</dd><br>
<dd>음악, 무용, 연극 등을 많은 사람들 앞에서 보이는 것.</dd><br>
<dd>Performing music, dance or a play in front of many people.</dd><br>
<dt>거행 [거ː행]</dt><br>
<dd>1. performance; conduct</dd><br>
<dd>시키는 대로 행함.</dd><br>
<dd>Acting on an order.</dd><br>
<dd>2. holding a ceremony</dd><br>
<dd>행사나 의식 등을 치름.</dd><br>
<dd>Performing an event, ceremony, etc.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>